id: pm-ypqp
title: Deduplicate templates package runtime and legacy command implementation
description: "Duplicate audit 2026-05-22: jscpd found src/cli/commands/templates.ts and packages/pm-templates/extensions/templates/runtime.ts carry nearly the same template normalization, option parsing, stored-template document parsing, reading, create execution, and list/apply branches. Representative clones include templates.ts:13-89 vs runtime.ts:63-138, templates.ts:89-113 vs runtime.ts:142-166, templates.ts:134-168 vs runtime.ts:180-214, and templates.ts:171-243 vs runtime.ts:211-283. Search found closed extraction item pm-2fgn and open package-first parent pm-59gj, but no active follow-up for this code drift. Fix by making the package runtime call a shared implementation or moving the legacy command to the package-backed runtime path, while preserving standalone package smoke behavior."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: code-quality,dedup,packages,templates
created_at: "2026-05-22T18:59:30.799Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T18:17:50.947Z"
author: codex-duplication-audit
acceptance_criteria: "Template name normalization, stored-template parsing, create-option mapping, and apply/list execution are single-sourced; src command and package runtime no longer diverge on template semantics; package smoke tests, templates unit tests, and pnpm build pass."
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Removed templates runtime duplication by making core templates command the single source and package runtime delegate through SDK.
expected_result: Template normalization/parsing/loading/list/show behavior is single-sourced while package smoke behavior remains intact.
actual_result: "Core owns builtins and template parsing; package runtime delegates; templates tests, manual dogfood, and full release gate passed."
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-23T17:46:02.570Z",templates-dedup-subagent,"Investigation note: current diff already adds builtin starter templates to package runtime/tests; core src/cli/commands/templates.ts still owns older stored-template parsing and loadCreateTemplateOptions. Scoped plan is to make src/cli/commands/templates.ts the single source including builtin behavior, then reduce package runtime ts/js to SDK-runtime delegation so standalone package behavior still loads through PM_CLI_PACKAGE_ROOT."
  "2026-05-23T17:49:28.219Z",templates-dedup-subagent,"Evidence: implemented templates dedup lane. src/cli/commands/templates.ts now owns builtin starter templates, template name normalization, stored-template parsing, option extraction, list/show resolution, and loadCreateTemplateOptions. packages/pm-templates/extensions/templates/runtime.ts and runtime.js now delegate save/list/show/loadCreateTemplateOptions to dist/sdk/index.js, preserving PM_CLI_PACKAGE_ROOT standalone loading while removing duplicated parser/normalizer code. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/templates-command.spec.ts (9 tests), pnpm build, pnpm exec tsc --noEmit, and linked pm test run test-local-mpin6hym-vc41rl passed all 3 commands."
